"title": "4122: Satan, as tempter",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4122",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's people are incited to evil by Satan. He seeks to exploit their weaknesses in order to deflect them from obedience to God.</p>\n<h2>Satan incites God's people to evil</h2>\n<h3>Satan exploits human weaknesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:5\">GEN 3:1–3:5</a></strong> <em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">Rev 12:9</a> identifies the serpent with Satan.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:4-Job2:5\">JOB 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:26-Eph4:27\">EPH 4:26–4:27</a></p>\n<h3>He tempts Christians to fall away</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:5\">1TH 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:31\">LUK 22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:26\">2TI 2:26</a></p>\n<h3>He inspires people to put God to the test</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3-Acts5:9\">ACT 5:3–5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:18\">PSA 78:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:41\">PSA 78:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:14\">PSA 106:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:10\">ACT 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:9\">1CO 10:9</a></p>\n<h3>He makes sin attractive</h3>\n<p>Lack of integrity:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:37\">MAT 5:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3\">ACT 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:14-1Tim5:15\">1TI 5:14–5:15</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:10-2Cor2:11\">2CO 2:10–2:11</a> <em>unforgiveness</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:14-Jas3:16\">JAS 3:14–3:16</a> <em>envy and selfish ambition</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is tempted by Satan</h2>\n<h3>In the wilderness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">MAT 4:1–4:11</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:13\">MRK 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Through Simon Peter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:23\">MAT 16:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:33\">MRK 8:33</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ identifies with believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:8\">HEB 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>Satan tests Christians</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:31\">LUK 22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:10\">REV 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Satan's temptations can be resisted</h2>\n<h3>By being alert</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:8\">1PE 5:8</a></strong></p>\n<h3>By prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:41\">MAT 26:41</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:38\">MRK 14:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:40\">LUK 22:40</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:13\">MAT 6:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:32\">LUK 22:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:46\">LUK 22:46</a></p>\n<h3>By relying on God's faithfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:13\">1CO 10:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:9\">2PE 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:10\">REV 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>By Jesus Christ's service as high priest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></p>",
